Philippine Stocks: Cebu Air, PAL Holdings, Robinsons Land Corp.

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-02-24T04:38:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/philippine-stocks-cebu-air-pal-holdings-robinsons-land-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the 12 p.m. close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index declined 0.7 percent to
3,730.84, the lowest level since Sept. 2.  Airlines:   Cebu Air Inc . (CEB PM), the nation’s biggest
budget carrier, slumped 4.6 percent to 79.10 pesos, the lowest
level since the shares began trading in October, on concern fuel
costs will rise as oil advanced for a sixth day in New York.  PAL
Holdings Inc . (PAL PM), owner of the nation’s biggest carrier,
sank 3.5 percent to 5.30 pesos, the steepest loss since Jan. 31.  Crude oil for April delivery increased 2.8 percent to
settle at $98.10 a barrel in New York yesterday, after earlier
reaching $100 a barrel for the first time since October 2008 on
speculation an uprising in Libya will disrupt supply.    Robinsons Land Corp . (RLC PM), the second-largest shopping
mall operator, decreased 1.9 percent to 11.68 pesos, the lowest
close since Feb. 11, 2010. President Frederick Go announced the
company plans to sell up to 13.6 billion pesos of stock to
existing shareholders in April.  “Investors are worried Robinsons may not attract demand
for its share sale because of the prevailing negative sentiment
on inflation and  interest rates ,” said Astro del Castillo,
managing director at First Grade Holdings Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
